The paper discusses the impact of model driven development on software development processes and the challenges faced by organizations in adopting it. This suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and software development (cs.SD). The paper also mentions the use of UML, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL). The assessment of usability through an empirical survey suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
